                                    <div class="wpfront-message wpfront-div">
                                        <h1>Securico Security Services in Zimbabwe</h1>
<p>The leading security company in the Zimbabwean Security Industry. Providing the highest possible standards of service delivery, training &amp; manpower development. Securico Security is ISO9001:2015 Quality Management Systems Certified by the Standards Association of Zimbabwe.</p>
<p>Our Services<br />From our Specialised training facility &amp; Dog section to Cash-in-Transit &amp; VIP Escort services, with Home &amp; Business security in between, we have a strong representation In all sectors of the economy.</p>
<p><br />Cash-In-Transit<br />Although principally used by financial Institutions, the Cash-in-Transit Division provides a wide range of services to suit various types of establishments in all sectors.</p>
<p><br />Mining Division<br />The Mining Division is managed by skilled personnel who have over 37 years’ experience in security. Their efforts are now entirely dedicated to security for the Mining Sector.</p>
<p><br />Service Guards<br />Static guards, Armed guards &amp; Guard dogs for all environments - including industrial properties, retailers, residences and embassies, high-rise buildings and offices, as well as mines.</p>
<p><br />Driver Simulation Courses<br />To properly determine the road-readiness of each of your employees, why not sign them up for a defensive driving assessment course with our new state-of-the-art driving simulator at our new training center.</p>
<p><br />Technical Services<br />Having established its brand in the security industry, Securico diversified into electronic security solutions in 2009. A wide range of products are available for differing environments. Systems can be designed to meet individual budgets.</p>
<p><br />Messenger Services<br />Save your business thousands of dollars every year in high delivery wages and increase efficiency and security by employing Securico's messengers.</p>
<p><br />Security Escort Services<br />Get a professional and experienced security detail trained specifically to escort important people and delegations during their stay in Zimbabwe.</p>
<p><br />Cashier Services<br />Introducing a smarter and much safer way to reconcile, transport and bank your daily cash takings. Get a Securico cashier today and enjoy the convenience of smart and safe business-to-bank security.</p>
<p><br />Solar Services<br />Many people in Zimbabwe are moving to supplement their electric power with renewable energy. We offer all-inclusive solar solutions tailor-made to suit your specific requirements.</p>
<p>Securico Security is one of the best security companies in Zimbabwe operating on international security standards. We are a dynamic security company with talented and experienced professionals making up the core of the business and making us the industry leaders in security services provision. By choosing us to be your security partners, our mandate is to provide you with tailored security services for your needs and keep you and your property safe whilst adhering to your requirements and objectives.</p>
<p><br />Security, Zimbabwe’s trusted name in private and corporate security services. From private investigations to executive background checks and security guard services, we provide a range of customer-focused solutions of all shapes and sizes across the country. Our cutting-edge security products, coupled together with a seasoned and dedicated team, have earned our brand a reputation as a formidable force within the security industry.</p>
<p>With over 2 decades in operation, we continue to provide our clients stellar services which are cost-effective and fully customized to their own unique environments. We take the time to understand your needs and deliver every promise to the best of all our entire resources – compromise is not an option when it comes to your security.</p>
<p><br />ZIMBABWE SECURITY SERVICES<br />Our security and emergency response coverage include Zimbabwe’s largest cities and most popular tourist destinations including Harare, Bulawayo, Chitungwiza, Mutare, the National Parks and many other destinations within the country.</p>
<p>When requiring immediate assistance for acts or threats of violence, personal health issues, vehicle accidents, political or social instability, natural disasters or any other sources of friction and uncertainty or when the need for intelligence gathering arises, Securico Security clients can contact us via our GPS beacons, satellite phones, mobile apps, or by texting or calling our 24-hour Global Operations Center, and we will immediately assist with the necessary resources, including personal security, vehicles, and aircraft if necessary.</p>
<p>Our carefully selected, vetted and tested security services in Zimbabwe are tailored to each client’s requirements, the threat, and the operating environment in which they are deployed. We can provide different levels of protection and offer security trained drivers, bodyguards, and high or low-profile protection teams throughout the country.</p>
<p><br />MANNED SECURITY<br />Security Solutions are customised to each client’s individual needs, using the most appropriate combination of manned guarding and security technology.</p>
<p>Armed Response<br />We have a reliable fleet of response vehicles manned by efficient, highly trained response officers.</p>
<p>SECURE MONITORING AND RESPONSE<br />Mobile security patrol and response services with state of the art alarm receiving and monitoring facilities.</p>
<p>Casual guarding<br />Throwing a party? Or just need extra security for a few hours?</p>
<p>CASH SOLUTIONS<br />We provide cash management solutions for a diverse range of organisations keeping your valuables and premises safe.</p>
<p>Localised security services<br />Your family and friends shouldn’t have to move through your community in fear of their safety.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>                                    </div>
                                                                                                       
                                    </td>
                                </tr>              
                            </table>
                            
                                    </div>
            </div>
            
